## 3. File and Directory Operations

| Command | Description | Example |
|---------|-------------|---------|
| `ls` | List directory contents | `ls` |
| `ls -l` | List with detailed information | `ls -l` |
| `ls -ltr` | List files by modification time | `ls -ltr` |
| `pwd` | Print working directory | `pwd` |
| `cd <dir>` | Change directory | `cd /home` |
| `mkdir <dir>` | Create a new directory | `mkdir newfolder` |
| `mkdir -p <path>` | Create nested directories | `mkdir -p app/logs/data` |
| `rm <file>` | Remove a file | `rm file.txt` |
| `rm -rf <dir>` | Force remove directory recursively | `rm -rf oldfolder` |
| `rmdir <dir>` | Remove empty directory | `rmdir newfolder` |
| `touch <file>` | Create an empty file | `touch newfile.txt` |
| `cp <src> <dest>` | Copy files and directories | `cp file.txt /backup/` |
| `mv <src> <dest>` | Move or rename files/directories | `mv old.txt new.txt` |
| `cat <file>` | Display file content | `cat file.txt` |
| `head <file>` | Display first 10 lines | `head -10 file.txt` |
| `tail <file>` | Display last 10 lines | `tail -10 file.txt` |
| `tail -f <file>` | Monitor file in real time | `tail -f /var/log/syslog` |
| `vi <file>` | Open file in vi editor | `vi file.txt` |
| `vim <file>` | Open file in vim editor | `vim file.txt` |

