## 11. File Transfer & Synchronization

| Command | Description | Example |
|---------|-------------|---------|
| `scp` | Securely copy files using SSH | `scp file.txt user@192.168.1.10:/home/user/` |
| `scp -r` | Copy directories recursively | `scp -r myfolder user@192.168.1.10:/home/user/` |
| `rsync` | Synchronize files/directories | `rsync -av file.txt /backup/` |
| `rsync -avz` | Sync with compression | `rsync -avz project/ user@192.168.1.10:/backup/` |
| `rsync --delete` | Delete extra destination files | `rsync -av --delete source/ backup/` |

